The paper deals with self-stabilizing protocols, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Distributed Systems (cs.DS) sub-categories. The focus on leader election and communication models suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of memory bits and node identifiers suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories.
